# Keyboard Shortcuts

## Suggested Example Pages For Shortcut Testing

Use these pages to demonstrate common shortcut flows in realistic contexts:

- Point-to-point navigation and query (`arrow keys`, `q`): [Column Unemployment Example](example-bar-comparison.md)
- Multi-series navigation (`arrow keys`, `home`, `end`, `[` and `]`): [Multi-Line Policy Rate and Unemployment](example-policy-unemployment-line.md)
- Sonification and speech toggles (`s`, `v`, `Ctrl`/`Escape`): [Stepline Live Policy-Rate Timeline](example-stepline-policy-rate-live.md)
- Outlier/relationship exploration (`q`, selection shortcuts): [Scatter Live Macro Relationship](example-scatter-macro-live.md)
- Category comparison with compact labels: [Bar Chart Electricity Top Movers](example-electricity-top-movers.md)

For full page coverage, start at [Example Gallery](exampleGallery.md).

